<p><strong>Daniel Simon</strong> is a poet, essayist, translator, and <em>WLT&rsquo;</em>s assistant director and editor in chief. His previous book, the edited volume <em>Nebraska Poetry: A Sesquicentennial Anthology, 1867&ndash;2017</em>, won a 2018 Nebraska Book Award.&nbsp;His most recent edited collection,&nbsp;<a href="https://deepvellum.org/product/dispatches-from-the-republic-of-letters/"><em>Dispatches from the Republic of Letters: 50 Years of the Neustadt International Prize for Literature</em></a>, was published by Deep Vellum&rsquo;s Phoneme imprint in 2020 and was nominated for a 2020 Foreword INDIES Award.</p>
